# API Endpoint Down
# 
# Simulate an unreachable API endpoint by using a dummy URL (e.g., http://localhost:9999) that does not respond.
# 
# Expected Behavior:
#   - The script logs retry attempts and sends a “down” notification.
#   - No recovery is logged since the endpoint remains unreachable.
# 
# Test command:
# `../check_endpoint.sh > api_down.log 2>&1`
# 
# Verify:
#   - Verify logs contain retry attempts and the “down” notification:
#     `grep "API endpoint is unavailable" api_down.log`
# 
HASS_API_URL="http://localhost:9999"  # Unreachable URL
HASS_AUTH_TOKEN="dummy_token"
SMS_TO="+1234567890"
SMS_FROM="sender@example.com"
ENDPOINT_DOWN_MESSAGE="API is down."
ENDPOINT_UP_MESSAGE="API is back online."